  "text": "Findings from the case-control comparison of neuropsychological performance are summarized in Table 3 and displayed in (Fig. 1) . In the domain of EF patients were impaired on working memory and attention, but no group differences were found for inhibition (Flanker and SART task) and verbal fluency. In the domain of delay aversion patients performed worse than controls on the delay discounting task, but not in the domain of timing (time estimation task). Across several tasks, patients were also more variable in their reaction times than controls. ANCOVA testing the effect of group for each neuropsychological measure, with age and gender as covariates. † Log-transformed variable to a normal distribution. n Indicates p-values surviving correction for the effective number of independent tests conducted (N=22, significance threshold (type 1 error rate at 5%)=0.0023) [CITATION_1] .",
